news.title: China Evergrande's unit receives liquidation order from Hong Kong court
news.para: The liquidators had filed a winding-up petition against company subsidiary CEG Holdings BVI in September, in a bid to recover funds from the debt-laden property company that defaulted in 2021 and triggered China's real estate market crisis.

news.title: EcoBox Industrial Parks acquires 50 acres of land in Chennai’s Mannur
news.para: The company is planning to undertake industrial and logistics development spread over 1.2 million sq ft with an investment of over Rs 400 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA limits SRO appointee tenure to two years
news.para: In a communication to the SROs, MahaRERA has directed to replace those representatives who have completed two years, with immediate effect.

news.title: Hyderabad's grade A office space occupancy to drop to 75.5-76% by March 2026: ICRA
news.para: Office supply grew at a higher compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of ~14% during FY 2017 to FY 2024 for the Hyderabad market, compared to a compound annual growth rate (CAGR) of ~7% for the six office markets in the country.

news.title: Alwar district administration begins shutting down illegal activities in Sariska reserve
news.para: The sub-divisional officer (SDO) of Thanagazi sent letters to the tehsildars of Thanagazi and Pratapgarh, alongside the Thanagazi Municipality, to implement the measures.

news.title: NGT issues show cause notices to Delhi DM and DJB CEO over illegal borewells
news.para: In its order dated January 8, the tribunal also directed all district magistrates to deposit Rs 10,000 each as costs for their failure to submit compliance reports.

news.title: Rajasthan government to re-auction mining plots
news.para: A senior official said, "Any plots with pending applications will be re-auctioned after the deadline. Notices were previously sent to these operators, and failure to comply will lead to the cancellation of their mining rights and the initiation of the e-auction process."

news.title: Land deal volume in India surge by 47% year-on-year across eight cities in 2024: Report
news.para: During 2024, nearly 135 land deals were closed compared to about 90 in 2023, primarily concentrated in major metropolitan areas such as Delhi-NCR, Bengaluru, Mumbai, Chennai, and Pune.

news.title: Puravankara posts pre-sales of Rs 1,265 crore in Q3 FY25
news.para: Puravankara's collections reached Rs 993 crore in Q3 FY25 compared to Rs 941 crores in Q3 FY24, up six per cent year-on-year.

news.title: Telangana CM seeks centre's help for second phase of Hyderabad metro rail
news.para: Participating at an event to release 'UNIKA'--autobiography of former Maharashtra Governor Ch Vidyasagar Rao here, Reddy said he had already requested the PM to cooperate in promoting Telangana to be a USD one trillion economy state in the country.

news.title: NCRTC begins trial runs of Meerut metro
news.para: The trial run involves testing the trains' tracks and traction. Initially, the trains are operated manually under the train control management system (TCMS).

news.title: Pune: Chakan village and surrounding areas to get separate civic bodies
news.para: According to sources, the talks of villages under Alandi, Chakan and Rajgurunagar municipal councils uniting under a new municipal corporation are under way.

news.title: Government land worth Rs 1,500 crore allegedly transferred to private individuals in Sircilla
news.para: The district administration has begun investigating the widespread land scam and identified that 1,300 acres to 1,400 acres of land was illegally grabbed, particularly in seven to eight villages along main roads.

news.title: Ranchi civic body issues warning to holding tax defaulters
news.para: The RMC has published a list of defaulters along with a notice, serving as a final warning for holding owners to comply with their tax obligations and avoid potential disruptions in their businesses.

news.title: Somwarpet delegation discusses C&D land issue with Karnataka forest chief
news.para: The delegation met him at the Forest Bhavan in Bengaluru to address the agricultural community's challenges and the uncertainty stemming from forest department interventions.

news.title: Gram chaupals playing key role in selecting PMAY beneficiaries in Uttar Pradesh
news.para: Conducted on the principle of ‘Problem of the Village – Solution in the Village,' where personal and public grievances of villagers are addressed directly within their communities, the Gram Chaupals are organised every Friday in two Gram Panchayats of each development block.

news.title: Sambhal: Over 110 plots near Sambhal stepwell sold using fake will
news.para: They added that the area was originally part of the Laxmanganj locality, but as the town developed, a new colony named ‘Mughalpura' emerged.

news.title: Godrej Properties launches its first project in Hyderabad
news.para: Situated on about three acres of land with an estimated booking value of approximately Rs 1,300 crore, Godrej Madison Avenue will feature 1.2 million sq ft of saleable area.

news.title: Kolkata metro plans to extend Joka-Esplanade purple line to Eden Gardens
news.para: This is good news not only for cricket and football lovers but also scores of people who commute daily to workplaces around Strand Road, Babughat, Calcutta High Court and BBD Bag.
